column5: Sounds like a fun day...and yes get a snow machine....I would not walk 10 feet for one of those slimy buggers!!!
Oh Emil, that sucks, the walking part I mean, nice that you actually caught fish.   pm me as Paul likes to go out more than I do and we have a snowmobile so you two could go out together
A good pair of snowshoes + Smitty sled does wonders......  Burt
For limiting out in 15 minutes I feel like the trek is worth it. That being said, I felt your pain reading that haul. Congrats on the beauty whitefish.
The price you pay for taking the unbeaten path Emil. Looks like a nasty day Sunday. Monday I might get out.  Nice fish.  BTW, your no spring chicken anymore. I feal your pain.LOL

Nice whities,feel your pain as well.The 1.5 km walk was not nice.Suvey stopped by,He came from Big Bay Point.Stopping at each hut he could on the way.Not one fish he saw of any size.Good to see you were one of the very few!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Nice report and nice fish! I know that feeling all too well (the walking part and sheer exhaustion) You have to admit though, at the end of the day when you finally make it back to your vehicle it's a pretty damn good feeling! I'm sure you wouldn't miss it too much once you get a sled though.
I would a been out there with you today for sure but was another busy day at the fishing show.   Maybe next weekend if I can get the sled running

great report and amazing that it only took you 15 minutes to catch those.  I would a been out there with you today for sure but was another busy day at the fishing show. Maybe next weekend if I can get the sled running  Where is the booth you are at located, going to the show tomorrow afternoon, as I believe I  mentioned in the other thread
What a day dude! Nice going on the dinner fish A machine is deff in your future for next year!! Let's get more Monday

The feeling never goes away.   I can't count the amout of Mondays my sled went to work in the bed of my truck because I was too exhausted to unload it Sunday night.      But sat. Morning your legs will defiantly thank you .

What a day dude! Nice going on the dinner fish A machine is deff in your future for next year!! Let's get more Monday   I think #720 rings a bell... He's paired up with a plastics supplier - Impact Baits.  I know he said he was with impact baits, just was curious of a rough location so thank you kenzy
I believe it's booth 703.  Right across from the sunglass  booth an right beside the perfect  jig.
I believe it's booth 703. Right across from the sunglass booth an right beside the perfect jig.  Thanks again, looking forward to meeting you and seeing your work
